"Higher values require one cell type to dominate the marker evidence; lowering this accepts weaker winners and reduces Ambiguous calls." = "较高值要求一种细胞类型明显主导标记物证据；降低该值会接受较弱的胜出者并减少模糊判定。";
"Minimum separation between the best and runner-up cell type. Increasing it makes mixed-marker cells more likely to remain Ambiguous; lowering it assigns borderline cells more aggressively." = "最佳和次佳细胞类型之间的最小差值。增大该值会使混合标记细胞更可能保持模糊；降低该值会更积极地分配边界细胞。";
