"Fix Voronoi radius at %@ um" = "将 Voronoi 半径固定为 %@ um";
"Fix buffer radius at %@ um" = "将缓冲半径固定为 %@ um";
"Voronoi ownership radius around each nucleus. Increasing it allows marker signal farther from the nucleus to contribute; lowering it keeps assignment closer to the nuclear center and can reduce spillover between crowded cells." = "每个细胞核周围的 Voronoi 归属半径。增大该值可纳入距离细胞核更远的标记信号；降低该值可使分配更靠近核中心，并减少拥挤细胞之间的信号串扰。";
"Extra buffer outside the nucleus used when sampling marker intensity. Increasing it captures membrane/cytoplasmic signal but may mix neighboring cells; lowering it is stricter and may miss broader cell boundaries." = "采样标记强度时使用的核外额外缓冲区。增大该值可捕获膜或细胞质信号，但可能混入邻近细胞；降低该值更严格，但可能遗漏较宽的细胞边界。";
"Marker voting radius for deciding positive markers. Larger values stabilize noisy channels and include peripheral signal; smaller values make assignments more local and sensitive to nuclear-adjacent intensity." = "用于判定阳性标记物的投票半径。较大值可稳定噪声通道并纳入外围信号；较小值使分配更局部，并对核周强度更敏感。";
"Background correction radius for marker channels. Increasing it removes broad background and uneven staining more strongly; lowering it preserves diffuse signal but may increase false positives." = "标记物通道的背景校正半径。增大该值会更强地去除宽广背景和不均匀染色；降低该值可保留弥散信号，但可能增加假阳性。";
"Smoothing applied before marker thresholding. Increasing it reduces speckle and isolated hot pixels but can blur small positive cells; lowering it keeps sharp signal and more noise." = "标记物阈值处理前的平滑。增大该值可减少散斑和孤立亮点，但可能模糊小型阳性细胞；降低该值可保留锐利信号，同时保留更多噪声。";
"Increasing this removes small noisy marker objects; lowering it allows small true positives but may add speckle-driven assignments." = "增大该值可移除小型噪声标记对象；降低该值允许小型真实阳性，但可能增加散斑驱动的分配。";
"Increasing this makes calls more conservative; lowering it increases sensitivity for weak or small marker-positive cells." = "增大该值会使判定更保守；降低该值会提高对弱信号或小型标记阳性细胞的敏感度。";

